annotationA: Cyclin-T; Regulatory subunit of the cyclin-dependent kinase pair (CDK9/cyclin T) complex, also called positive transcription elongation factor B (P-TEFb), which is proposed to facilitate the transition from abortive to production elongation by phosphorylating the CTD (carboxy-terminal domain) of the large subunit of RNA polymerase II (RNAP II)
annotationB: Transcription factor IIB (TFIIB) is a basal transcription factor that binds to the TATA box-binding protein. TFIIB is required for the initiation of transcription by RNA polymerase II
